Package: dehex
Title: Learn to Roughly Assess Colour Hex Codes By Eye
Version: 0.1.2
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Matt",
           family = "Dray",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "mwdray@gmail.com")
Description: Follow David DeSandro's method to quickly generate a rough colour
    name (e.g. 'light washed yellow') by looking only at its hex code (e.g. 
    #F2D359). Contains standalone functions and a Shiny app for learning the
    process interactively.
URL: https://github.com/matt-dray/dehex
BugReports: https://github.com/matt-dray/dehex/issues
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
